cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.CG, cs.MM, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with 3D shape analysis and representation, which is a common topic in computer graphics (cs.GR) and computer vision (cs.CV). The use of quasi-geodesic paths and normal curvature suggests a focus on computational geometry (cs.CG). The proposed shape descriptor and its comparison with other state-of-the-art descriptors indicates a potential overlap with multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
